 <text id="B0007T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>McDonnell discusses the terms by which a teacher will be hired in Waynesboro.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A L.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Head Quarters">H<hi rend="super">d</hi> Qrs.</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr><abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
     <name type="recipient">Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A Com<hi rend="super">r</hi></abbr><lb/>Staunton, Va</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1868-11-19">Nov. 19/68</date>
      <name type="place">Winchester, Va.</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Sir,</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>In reply to your application for a teacher at Waynesboro, I have to state that Mr. Brackett
     will furnish a teacher on the following terms; the freedmen to board him, furnish fuel + pay
     him $10 per <abbr expan="month">mo.</abbr></p>

    <p>Mr. Waring a very intelligent colored man representing another society which is operating in
     the Valley will furnish a teacher if they will pay him $5 per month and fuel etc. for the
     school. </p>

    <p>Please ascertain at once which proposition (if either) they accept. I would of course
     recommend the latter.</p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
     <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant">Asst</abbr>
      <abbr expan="Commissioner">Comr</abbr></signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
